<p><strong>Short-form:</strong> How can I achieve a read-only style wrapper div in the editor that also appears in the source?</p>  <p><strong>Detail:</strong> CKEditor is applied through textarea method. Users select the Templates plugin and choose their respective div-based template, then fill the populated divs with their relevant content. </p>  <p>75% of user want to copy their source code and then paste it in their relevant platform; the remaining users will be using the Save button/plugin.</p>  <p>I need to ensure all the template-generated divs (which are a collection of parent-sibling-child divs) are <strong>ONLY</strong> placed inside a single WRAPPER div.</p>  <p><strong>Example:</strong> </p>  <pre class="lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;div class="wrapper"&gt; &lt;!--this is the very important wrapper div--&gt;     &lt;div class="container"&gt; &lt;!--this is the start of the template divs--&gt;         &lt;div class="headingbox"&gt;             heading         &lt;/div&gt;         &lt;div class="textbox"&gt;             Text         &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;div class="container"&gt;         &lt;div class="headingbox"&gt;             heading         &lt;/div&gt;         &lt;div class="textbox"&gt;             Text         &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;!--etc etc, template divs end--&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I've tried adding the WRAPPER div to the textarea, which works initially, but when I use the Template plugin, the generated divs are created in multiple instances of the wrapper, instead of being added as sibling divs inside the wrapper div.</p>  <p><strong>Question:</strong> How can I achieve a read-only style wrapper div in the editor that also appears in the source?</p>